    <div class="db-overview">
        <h2>The Gateway to <span>Central Sarawak</span></h2>
        <p>Sibu is one of the major towns in Sarawak, located along the mighty Rajang River — the longest river in Malaysia. Known as the "Gateway to Central Sarawak," Sibu boasts a rich Chinese heritage, especially from the Fuzhou (Foochow) settlers who arrived in the early 1900s.</p>
        <p>The town is famous for its vibrant markets, historic Chinese temples, and unique culinary offerings like Kampua Mee and Kompia buns. Sibu's architectural landscape is distinctly shaped by its Foochow community, with many historical shophouses that remain central to the thriving local business scene.</p>
        <p>Sibu's charm lies in its authentic blend of culture, food, and the bustling energy of its local communities. It's also the gateway to rural longhouses, riverine journeys, and the surrounding rainforest wilderness of Borneo.</p>
        <div class="db-overview-tags">
            <span class="db-overview-tag">🏙️ Gateway City</span>
            <span class="db-overview-tag">🌊 Rajang River</span>
            <span class="db-overview-tag">🏛️ Foochow Heritage</span>
            <span class="db-overview-tag">🍜 Iconic Food</span>
            <span class="db-overview-tag">🌿 Borneo Rainforest</span>
            <span class="db-overview-tag">🛒 Largest Indoor Market</span>
        </div>
    </div>

